The 2018 Comrades Marathon saw a diverse range of dedicated, talented contestants.
Amputee runner Xolani Luvuno, a former drug addict and cancer survivor, finished the Comrades on crutches.
The winner of the race, Bongumusa Mthembu, is only the second South African to win the event twice.
READ MORE: Comrades Marathon: Who to watch
But another contestant seemed to have had a grand time, dancing at a water stop during the race. Volunteers joined in, making it a very entertaining few minutes.

Video Playerhttps://citizen.co.za/wp-content/uploads/sites/18/2018/06/comrades-video-whatsapp.mp400:0000:0000:00Use Up/Down Arrow keys to increase or decrease volume.
 
The man, whose name is not yet known, ditched his time concerns for fancy dance moves before returning to the race.
The video has been circulating on social media, and highlights an aspect of the race that many do not consider – it is about having fun and coming together. And it seems that the jovial gentleman successfully did both.
